docclass article

importpkg { tikz }

startdoc

useenv figure [ht] {
    \centering
    useenv tikzpicture {
    % NOTE: python does not allow outermost indentation
    pycode {
import vesti
import math

i = 0
while i < 2 * math.pi:
    xcos_val = i * math.cos(i)
    xsin_val = i * math.sin(i)
    vesti.sprintn(f"\\draw (0,0) -- ({xcos_val},{xsin_val});")
    i += 0.01
    }
}}

Now, pycode{import vesti;vesti.sprint(f"{2**100}")} can be embedded.
